00:41:20,438 --> 00:41:22,758
"<i>George said the Mr Philips would
be a witness against me</i>."

729
00:41:23,258 --> 00:41:24,295
"<i>A witness</i>."

730
00:41:30,020 --> 00:41:31,779
I'll see that you get
another prescription.

731
00:41:32,085 --> 00:41:33,901
"<i>Yes, you just get in
touch with Dr Grahame</i>."

732
00:41:35,419 --> 00:41:37,674
"<i>Why didn't I tell him about George?</i>"

733
00:41:45,634 --> 00:41:46,506
"<i>The letter</i>."

734
00:41:47,308 --> 00:41:48,724
"<i>I had to get that letter back</i>."

735
00:41:50,258 --> 00:41:52,907
"<i>I couldn't tell anyone about
George until I got that letter back</i>."

736
00:41:54,195 --> 00:41:56,193
"<i>I could feel the woman
next door watching</i>."

737
00:41:57,867 --> 00:42:00,122
"<i>Maybe she'd be a
witness against me too</i>."

738
00:42:00,849 --> 00:42:03,519
"<i>She could tell them how
I ran out of the house</i>."

739
00:42:04,117 --> 00:42:05,466
"<i>And then back in again</i>."

740
00:42:06,189 --> 00:42:07,751
"<i>How strangely I was acting</i>."

741
00:42:10,023 --> 00:42:12,929
"<i>It wouldn't matter what she thought
if I could only get that letter back</i>."

742
00:42:14,265 --> 00:42:16,806
"<i>Then I tried to think.
Which way did he go?</i>"

743
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:38,544
What's that for, Tex?

744
00:42:39,066 --> 00:42:39,852
Who knows?

745
00:42:40,199 --> 00:42:42,089
The engine needs everything
we can put in it.

746
00:42:42,189 --> 00:42:43,449
Yeah, but what will it do?

747
00:42:44,037 --> 00:42:44,823
Who cares?

748
00:42:45,283 --> 00:42:46,169
Pardon me.

749
00:42:46,642 --> 00:42:48,630
Can you tell me, did the
postman go by here yet?

750
00:42:48,894 --> 00:42:49,995
The postman?
- Yeah.

751
00:42:50,388 --> 00:42:52,880
That old oddball found his way
through here a little while ago.

752
00:42:53,129 --> 00:42:54,902
Oh. Which way did he go? Do you know?

753
00:42:55,859 --> 00:42:57,373
Thataway.
- Oh, thanks.

754
00:42:57,875 --> 00:43:00,609
The way toward Merritt Street. You know?
- Yeah, I know.

755
00:43:06,687 --> 00:43:07,685
Oh, I'm sorry.

756
00:43:17,782 --> 00:43:20,793
You know, every time I go home
at night I always tell my wife Laura.

757
00:43:21,221 --> 00:43:24,521
If it wasn't for that pension
plan I do I'd just never get up.

758
00:43:24,730 --> 00:43:27,459
I'd just drop in my tracks one of
these days and that would settle it.

759
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:29,810
And I'd just never get up
anymore and that's all.

760
00:43:30,178 --> 00:43:31,869
You know how it is.
- Hello, Mr Carson.

761
00:43:32,536 --> 00:43:34,105
See you later, Joe.
- See you later.

762
00:43:34,406 --> 00:43:37,162
Well, Moss Jones. What are
you doing out this way?

763
00:43:38,431 --> 00:43:40,465
I was visiting a friend.
- Oh, that's nice.

764
00:43:40,796 --> 00:43:42,936
I wish I had more time for visitors.

765
00:43:43,327 --> 00:43:46,652
But by the time I get home at night I
can just hardly make it up the stairs.

766
00:43:47,603 --> 00:43:50,029
Mr Carston, remember that
letter I gave you this morning?

767
00:43:50,585 --> 00:43:53,227
I suppose so. I pick up plenty
of letters. Why, what about it?

768
00:43:53,472 --> 00:43:55,171
Well, I know it seems silly but I ..

769
00:43:55,965 --> 00:43:58,145
I mailed it by mistake.
It wasn't even finished. Yes.

770
00:43:58,245 --> 00:43:59,567
What did you do that for?

771
00:43:59,667 --> 00:44:01,490
I don't know, I guess
I was just so busy I ..

772
00:44:01,590 --> 00:44:04,886
Finish it up and mail the rest tomorrow.
They'll get it in two instalments.

773
00:44:05,113 --> 00:44:06,529
You wouldn't want me to do that.

774
00:44:06,968 --> 00:44:08,492
May I have the letter please?

775
00:44:10,705 --> 00:44:13,523
So, I pick them up and carry them around
for miles and then they want them back.

776
00:44:13,865 --> 00:44:15,989
Well, I'm sorry but you
can understand why.

777
00:44:16,245 --> 00:44:18,543
I wouldn't want it to go out unfinished.
- Yeah, I guess so.

778
00:44:18,731 --> 00:44:21,520
But all these delays count. Keep me
on my feet longer than I ought to.

779
00:44:21,787 --> 00:44:23,573
It won't be much trouble will it?

780
00:44:23,942 --> 00:44:25,329
Here. Here it is.
- Thank you.

781
00:44:25,466 --> 00:44:28,224
Now look, you shouldn't have given
me this letter in the first place.

782
00:44:28,428 --> 00:44:29,160
Why?

783
00:44:29,371 --> 00:44:32,331
Giving me this letter is just
like putting it in a mailbox.

784
00:44:32,521 --> 00:44:35,382
Now, you wouldn't expect to get this
back from the mailbox would you?

785
00:44:36,224 --> 00:44:38,995
No. But surely you can make
this exception. After all, I ..

786
00:44:41,563 --> 00:44:44,059
Isn't this fellow the district attorney?

787
00:44:45,070 --> 00:44:45,754
Yes.

788
00:44:46,617 --> 00:44:49,293
Yes. My husband read about
some graft in the newspaper.

789
00:44:49,393 --> 00:44:51,274
And wrote to the district
attorney about it.

790
00:44:51,452 --> 00:44:53,494
Oh, your husband wrote the letter?
- Yes.

791
00:44:53,747 --> 00:44:55,203
I thought you said you wrote it.

792
00:44:55,786 --> 00:44:57,654
Well, what's the difference?
He is my husband.

793
00:44:57,754 --> 00:44:59,909
It makes all the difference
in the world, Mrs Jones.

794
00:45:00,187 --> 00:45:02,182
But why?
- It's one of our strictest rules.

795
00:45:02,605 --> 00:45:05,637
We can't return a letter to anyone
except the person who wrote it.

796
00:45:06,453 --> 00:45:08,699
But Mr Carston, my husband
is sick. You know that.

797
00:45:08,976 --> 00:45:11,164
And he sent me to get the letter back.
- Yes. I know that.

798
00:45:11,462 --> 00:45:12,778
Don't be so obstinate!

799
00:45:12,878 --> 00:45:14,800
You know it's alright.
He's sick. Give it to me.

800
00:45:14,900 --> 00:45:16,445
Obstinate? Now how do you like that?

801
00:45:16,867 --> 00:45:19,904
After standing here patiently in all
this heat trying to reason with you.

802
00:45:20,576 --> 00:45:24,014
You are the one being obstinate and
don't realise it's against the rules.

803
00:45:24,114 --> 00:45:25,905
What do you care if
it's against the rules?

804
00:45:26,005 --> 00:45:27,657
I have to care but you don't.

805
00:45:28,346 --> 00:45:29,876
You are not the one who'd get fired.

806
00:45:32,125 --> 00:45:32,911
I'm sorry.

807
00:45:33,252 --> 00:45:34,563
I'm very sorry, Mr Carston.

808
00:45:34,848 --> 00:45:37,380
I forgot what it means to you.
Your responsibility.

809
00:45:38,543 --> 00:45:39,933
It must be this terrible heat.

810
00:45:40,724 --> 00:45:41,478
Please.

811
00:45:41,867 --> 00:45:44,060
I know how anxious my husband
is to get that letter back.

812
00:45:45,003 --> 00:45:47,027
It was my fault you see,
I mailed it by mistake.

813
00:45:47,548 --> 00:45:50,196
He's awfully with me. He is
very angry with me, Mr Carston.

814
00:45:50,726 --> 00:45:52,027
Couldn't you please help me?

815
00:45:52,478 --> 00:45:54,153
Couldn't I please have the letter back?

816
00:45:55,108 --> 00:45:57,274
Well, I tell you what I'll do.
- Yes?

817
00:45:58,038 --> 00:46:00,501
I'm all through with the route
until this afternoon's delivery.

818
00:46:00,764 --> 00:46:02,895
Since it is so important like you say.
- Oh, it is.

819
00:46:03,429 --> 00:46:06,892
If you give me a lift to town in your
car so I won't lose any more time ..

820
00:46:06,992 --> 00:46:07,709
I will.

821
00:46:07,809 --> 00:46:10,964
I'll go to your house with you now and
give the letter to Mr Jones personally.

822
00:46:12,004 --> 00:46:13,953
No, you can't.
- But, Mrs Jones ..

823
00:46:14,154 --> 00:46:17,013
This way I'll be sticking to the rules
and your husband gets his letter back.

824
00:46:17,314 --> 00:46:18,930
But my husband didn't sleep last night.

825
00:46:19,278 --> 00:46:21,809
And he fell asleep just before I left
and I wouldn't want to wake him.

826
00:46:22,069 --> 00:46:24,251
I'm trying to do the right thing
by everybody concerned.

827
00:46:24,687 --> 00:46:28,305
It seems you cannot cooperate. I'm not
risking losing my job for anybody.

828
00:46:28,405 --> 00:46:31,442
Try to understand.
- I can't talk about it any longer.

829
00:46:31,672 --> 00:46:32,935
I can't waste more time.

830
00:46:33,035 --> 00:46:35,681
Do you want me to take the letter to
your husband personally or don't you?

831
00:46:36,660 --> 00:46:37,246
No.

832
00:46:37,364 --> 00:46:39,985
Alright then. I'll take it to the
post office like I'm supposed to.

833
00:46:40,406 --> 00:46:42,920
You can go down there and
get it from the superintendent.

834
00:46:43,262 --> 00:46:44,617
Superintendent?
- Yeah.

835
00:46:44,816 --> 00:46:47,126
He has more authority than I have.
Maybe he'll give it to you.

836
00:46:47,226 --> 00:46:48,003
I see.

837
00:46:48,103 --> 00:46:49,695
You'd better not waste any more time.

838
00:46:49,905 --> 00:46:52,463
Once I bring the mail in
they send it out right quick.

839
00:46:52,687 --> 00:46:55,402
Once it leaves the post office
for delivery nobody can stop it.

840
00:46:55,502 --> 00:46:57,000
The post office downtown?
- Yep.

841
00:46:57,116 --> 00:46:58,595
Thanks. Oh, Mr Carston.

842
00:46:59,125 --> 00:47:00,913
How do I get there?
The shortest way I mean.

843
00:47:01,013 --> 00:47:03,195
Right down the boulevard
is the shortest. Can't miss it.

844
00:47:03,295 --> 00:47:04,723
Thanks. How much time do I have?

845
00:47:05,186 --> 00:47:07,417
About 2:30. Maybe a little over 4.

846
00:47:07,740 --> 00:47:08,713
Thank you.

847
00:47:44,225 --> 00:47:45,071
Ellen.

848
00:47:46,545 --> 00:47:47,512
Ellen!

849
00:48:37,942 --> 00:48:38,728
Pardon me.

850
00:48:39,315 --> 00:48:39,970
Yes?

851
00:48:40,070 --> 00:48:41,980
Have you seen Mrs Jones this morning?

852
00:48:42,473 --> 00:48:44,914
Yes. She went out about a half hour ago.

853
00:48:45,112 --> 00:48:46,341
Went out?
- Yes.

854
00:48:46,671 --> 00:48:48,473
But what about George? Mr Jones?

855
00:48:48,755 --> 00:48:50,642
She hasn't gone off and
left him alone has she?

856
00:48:51,196 --> 00:48:52,905
Well ..
- Her husband is sick you know.

857
00:48:53,403 --> 00:48:54,304
So I've heard.

858
00:48:55,159 --> 00:48:57,736
If course I never really met them.
Though I haven't lived here long.

859
00:48:57,943 --> 00:48:59,895
I can't imagine her going off like that.

860
00:49:00,966 --> 00:49:05,003
I'm, Mr Jones' aunt. I made him some
jelly consomm. I packed it in ice.

861
00:49:05,663 --> 00:49:06,585
It's melting.

862
00:49:06,837 --> 00:49:09,025
I never dreamt I wouldn't get in.

863
00:49:09,812 --> 00:49:11,285
I could tell you where the key is.

864
00:49:11,746 --> 00:49:12,528
Key?

865
00:49:12,807 --> 00:49:16,359
Perhaps you think it's nosy but I did
see her when she locked the door.

866
00:49:16,948 --> 00:49:18,278
Well, isn't that good of you.

867
00:49:18,867 --> 00:49:20,298
The front door?
- Yes.

868
00:49:20,707 --> 00:49:22,279
Right over there above the door.

869
00:49:22,684 --> 00:49:23,470
Thank you.

870
00:49:23,925 --> 00:49:26,190
I don't know how you stand
it in the sun without a hat on.

871
00:49:26,290 --> 00:49:27,648
You might dry up like a prune.

872
00:49:32,722 --> 00:49:35,201
The top of the green shutter.
The far side of the door.

873
00:49:36,809 --> 00:49:37,746
I've found it.

874
00:49:38,518 --> 00:49:40,506
If there is anything I can
do for you just call me.

875
00:49:40,670 --> 00:49:42,530
You are very kind. Thank you.

876
00:50:21,300 --> 00:50:22,144
Aunt Clara.

877
00:50:22,360 --> 00:50:24,145
Ellen, where on earth have you been?

878
00:50:25,055 --> 00:50:26,370
Have you been upstairs?

879
00:50:26,558 --> 00:50:28,933
I was just going up.
Why are you so out of breath?

880
00:50:30,088 --> 00:50:30,771
Why?

881
00:50:31,630 --> 00:50:32,645
I've been running.

882
00:50:32,745 --> 00:50:35,023
Running in all this heat?
You should have more sense.

883
00:50:36,251 --> 00:50:38,619
How did you get in, aunt Clara?
- I found the key on the ledge.

884
00:50:38,993 --> 00:50:41,218
There, look at that.
Slipped right down my dress.

885
00:50:41,641 --> 00:50:42,624
Now it's ruined.

886
00:50:42,955 --> 00:50:45,412
I was worried half to death.
I thought something had happened.

887
00:50:46,402 --> 00:50:48,118
I've never known you
to go out like this.

888
00:50:48,308 --> 00:50:49,209
How is George?

889
00:50:49,528 --> 00:50:50,431
He's alright.

890
00:50:50,531 --> 00:50:52,512
I even rang the bell. Just a jab.

891
00:50:53,127 --> 00:50:54,628
Did he take one of those sedatives?

892
00:50:54,824 --> 00:50:55,455
Yes.

893
00:50:55,686 --> 00:50:58,005
People take too much medicine
nowadays if you ask me.

894
00:50:58,591 --> 00:51:01,201
When I was a girl we
had homeopathic doctors.

895
00:51:01,690 --> 00:51:03,137
I wonder what happened to them.

896
00:51:03,237 --> 00:51:06,260
Anyway, they gave very little medicine
and it all tasted good, even the tonics.

897
00:51:06,624 --> 00:51:08,339
And no promises at all.

898
00:51:08,707 --> 00:51:10,781
Ellen, I've never seen you
look so tired and worn out.

899
00:51:10,881 --> 00:51:12,841
Why not ask that doctor
to give you something?

900
00:51:12,941 --> 00:51:13,784
I'm alright.

901
00:51:14,179 --> 00:51:16,123
He looks too young to
me to be a good doctor.

902
00:51:16,223 --> 00:51:18,239
But after all, if you and
George like him so much ..

903
00:51:18,399 --> 00:51:19,902
Confidence is half the battle.

904
00:51:20,324 --> 00:51:21,835
You look awful peaky.

905
00:51:22,291 --> 00:51:24,193
Ellen, you are not letting
yourself go, are you?

906
00:51:24,513 --> 00:51:26,156
No. I know I look terrible.

907
00:51:27,226 --> 00:51:28,804
Look, when George fell asleep, I ..

908
00:51:29,574 --> 00:51:30,831
I had some errands to do.

909
00:51:32,724 --> 00:51:33,780
I'll get you some.

910
00:51:35,803 --> 00:51:38,436
I just thought I would go and
take care of them without ..

911
00:51:38,860 --> 00:51:39,932
Bothering to change.

912
00:51:40,725 --> 00:51:42,490
You know how it is.
- Sure you are alright?

913
00:51:42,590 --> 00:51:43,276
Yes.

914
00:51:43,376 --> 00:51:46,576
Why not go upstairs and lie down for a
bit. Take a snooze. It will do you good.

915
00:51:47,273 --> 00:51:49,004
I'm not tired. Really I'm not.

916
00:51:49,512 --> 00:51:51,193
Well, after all.

917
00:51:52,132 --> 00:51:53,874
Clara, I have so much to do today.

918
00:51:54,130 --> 00:51:55,283
Do sit down, Ellen.

919
00:51:56,186 --> 00:51:57,408
Lean back. Relax.

920
00:51:59,229 --> 00:52:01,718
You'll be on <i>your </i>back before you
know it if you don't watch out.

921
00:52:02,305 --> 00:52:04,317
After all, all I want to do is to help.

922
00:52:04,864 --> 00:52:06,793
From now on, I'm going
to have more time too.

923
00:52:07,122 --> 00:52:08,647
Ellen, I forgot to tell you.

924
00:52:08,990 --> 00:52:09,894
I resigned.

925
00:52:10,827 --> 00:52:11,632
Resigned?

926
00:52:11,732 --> 00:52:15,047
From the Helper's Guild after fifteen
years. I'm not helping anymore.

927
00:52:17,197 --> 00:52:17,955
I will ..

928
00:52:18,283 --> 00:52:21,617
I'll leave the kitchen door open and we
can talk as I clean out there. Alright?

929
00:52:21,717 --> 00:52:23,292
You might as well. You're so fidgety.

930
00:52:24,161 --> 00:52:27,391
Oh, Ellen. While you are on your
feet will you bring me a dishcloth?

931
00:52:28,621 --> 00:52:30,774
For fifteen years I was in that guild.

932
00:52:31,131 --> 00:52:32,952
And for the past five I was treasurer.

933
00:52:33,140 --> 00:52:36,206
And for the last three they were
promising me the presidency.

934
00:52:36,619 --> 00:52:37,605
So, what happens?

935
00:52:37,765 --> 00:52:39,711
Last Tuesday they elect Paula Comstock.

936
00:52:39,811 --> 00:52:41,637
You know, Zachary's wife?
Well I was furious.

937
00:52:41,835 --> 00:52:44,562
Zachary said I was hasty.
But after fifteen years ..

938
00:52:44,868 --> 00:52:47,000
You know, I've never known
a small woman yet ..

939
00:52:47,100 --> 00:52:49,527
Who wasn't always boasting about
her little hands and tiny feet.

940
00:52:49,627 --> 00:52:51,840
And trying to run everything.
- That's the best I can do.

941
00:52:51,940 --> 00:52:53,185
Do you think I was right?

942
00:52:53,909 --> 00:52:55,324
Fifteen years, after all.

943
00:52:55,424 --> 00:52:58,629
Zachary was upset. He says I
need lots of outside activity. Lots.

944
00:52:58,882 --> 00:53:00,226
And I agreed with him.

945
00:53:02,835 --> 00:53:05,419
"<i>I thought if she
didn't stop I'd scream</i>."

946
00:53:09,119 --> 00:53:11,622
I always tell him he plays
too much at his age.

947
00:53:11,936 --> 00:53:14,339
That's just one of the worries of
being married to an older man.

948
00:53:14,557 --> 00:53:16,849
Ellen, why don't you have
some of that jelly consomm?

949
00:53:16,949 --> 00:53:20,960
At least it was jelly when I left home.
Try it. It's tasty and full of vitamins.

950
00:53:21,435 --> 00:53:24,150
I'd like someone to enjoy it.
After all it ruined my dress.

951
00:53:24,371 --> 00:53:27,042
I think I'll run up
and pop in on George.

952
00:53:27,310 --> 00:53:29,746
If he is asleep you can tell
him later that I peeped in.

953
00:53:33,750 --> 00:53:36,238
Aunt Clara. Aunt Clara.
- What is it, darling?

954
00:53:37,289 --> 00:53:39,965
There is something I must tell you.
- What is it, dear? What is the matter?

955
00:53:40,949 --> 00:53:41,632
I ..

956
00:53:41,825 --> 00:53:43,900
Are you having trouble?
- Yes.

957
00:53:45,637 --> 00:53:47,595
I didn't want to tell you
but now I think I must.

958
00:53:47,809 --> 00:53:48,501
Don't.

959
00:53:48,725 --> 00:53:51,936
Take my advice and don't. You will
only be sorry later that you did.

960
00:53:53,119 --> 00:53:55,072
I thought It was funny
you being out like that ..

961
00:53:55,172 --> 00:53:57,435
And not going up to see
George when you came in.

